<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">The Beals index is defined as: 
 <disp-formula id="eqn-1" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="peerj-07-6731-e001.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$${P_{ij}} = {1 \over {{S_i} - {I_{ij}}}}\sum\limits_{k \ne j} {{{{N_{jk}}{I_{ik}}} \over {{N_k}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="mml-eqn-1" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       <mi class="mi">j</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">S</mi>
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       </msub>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">I</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">i</mi>
         <mi class="mi">j</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mstyle displaystyle="true" class="mstyle">
      <munder class="munder">
       <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">k</mi>
        <mo class="mo">≠</mo>
        <mi class="mi">j</mi>
       </mrow>
      </munder>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mfrac class="mfrac">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">j</mi>
           <mi class="mi">k</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">I</mi>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
           <mi class="mi">k</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">N</mi>
          <mi class="mi">k</mi>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">P</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
  <italic class="italic">j</italic>
 </sub> is the probability that species 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic> will occur at community 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">S</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> is the number of species at community 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">I</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">ij</italic>
 </sub> is the incidence (0, 1) of species 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic> at community 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>. 
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">jk</italic>
 </sub> is the number of joint occurrence of species 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> (
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> ≠ 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>) at community 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">I</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">ik</italic>
 </sub> is the incidence (0, 1) of species 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> at community 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>, and 
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">k</italic>
 </sub> is the number of occurrences of species 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> (for further details, see 
 <xref rid="ref-38" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">Münzbergová &amp; Herben (2004)</xref> and 
 <xref rid="ref-31" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">Lewis, Szava-Kovats &amp; Pärtel (2016)</xref>).
</p>
